We continue the traversal for t seconds. At each step, if the traversal time (t) is zero or the frog reaches the target vertex, we store the probability of reaching the target vertex into the answer.

Upon completion of the DFS traversal, we return the final answer, which is the probability of the frog being on the vertex target after t seconds.

